title: Kind: Instances Overview
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

\import [[$:/plugins/rimir/kind/engine]] [[$:/plugins/rimir/kind/graph]]

! 🕸️ Kind: Instances Overview

A graph of every [[kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance in the wiki. Nodes start on a stable grid; **drag a node to reposition it — that position is saved** (to `$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/structure`) and restored on reload. Double-click a node to open it, hover for a tooltip — the tooltip offers ''edit'' (live field editor), ''delete'' (with confirmation; disabled while the node still has children) and ''Add child'' buttons for every kind whose `parent` field accepts this node's type, opening a create form with the parent pre-filled. Tick edge fields to draw those relationships; untick a type to hide its instances.

<style>
.kg-controls { display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:6px; }
.kg-controls label { white-space:nowrap; cursor:pointer; }
.kg-controls .kg-legend { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; font-weight:500; background:none; border:none; padding:0; cursor:pointer; }
</style>

<$let
  selFields={{{ [[$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/edge-fields]get[fields]] }}}
  hiddenTypes={{{ [[$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/hidden-types]get[hidden]] }}}
>

<div class="kg-controls">
<$edit-text tiddler="$:/state/rimir/kind/instances-overview/search" tag="input" placeholder="Search nodes…" class="tc-edit-texteditor" default="" style="flex:0 0 220px;"/>
<span style="opacity:0.7;">Edges:</span>
<$list filter="[function[kg.ref-fields]]" variable="_rf">
<label><$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/edge-fields" listField="fields" checked=<<_rf>>/> <$text text=<<_rf>>/></label>
</$list>
</div>

<div class="kg-controls">
<span style="opacity:0.7;">Types:</span>
<$list filter="[function[kg.type-keys]]" variable="_tk">
<$let
  _c={{{ [function[kg.color-of],<_tk>] }}}
  _ih={{{ [<hiddenTypes>enlist-input[]match<_tk>count[]] }}}
  _without={{{ [<hiddenTypes>enlist-input[]] -[<_tk>] +[join[ ]] }}}
  _with={{{ [<hiddenTypes>enlist-input[]] [<_tk>] +[unique[]join[ ]] }}}
>
<$button class="kg-legend" style={{{ [<_c>addprefix[color:]] }}}>
<$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/hidden-types" $field="hidden" $value={{{ [<_ih>compare:integer:gt[0]then<_without>] ~[<_with>] }}}/>
<$text text={{{ [<_ih>compare:integer:gt[0]then[☐]] ~[[☑]] }}}/> <$text text=<<_tk>>/>
</$button>
</$let>
</$list>
</div>

<%if [[$:/plugins/flibbles/graph]is[tiddler]] %>
<div class="boundingbox" style="height:95vh; min-height:480px;">
<$let searchText={{{ [[$:/state/rimir/kind/instances-overview/search]get[text]] }}}>
<$transclude $variable="kg-graph"
  nodeFilter="[all[tiddlers]has[kind.type]!has[kind.fields]search:caption,title<searchText>] :filter[function[kg.type-shown],<currentTiddler>,<hiddenTypes>]"
  selFields=<<selFields>>
  dataTiddler="$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/structure"
  physics="no"
  $mode="block"/>
</$let>
</div>
<%else%>
<div style="border:1px solid #d9a300; background:rgba(217,163,0,0.08); border-radius:6px; padding:12px 16px;">
This overview renders an interactive graph and needs a graph engine. Install ''[ext[flibbles/graph|https://flibbles.github.io/tw5-graph/]]'' plus a rendering engine (e.g. ''flibbles/vis-network'' or ''rimir/cytoscape-engine''), then reload. The edge / type controls above still work once an engine is present.
</div>
<%endif%>

</$let>
